channel.title: Missing File in VB6
channel.description:
ok so today i was making a web-browser and i did CTRL+T and clicked internet controls and got this
[code]File not found: 'C:\WINDOWS\system32\ieframe.dll\1'[/code]
what should i do?

item.title: Missing File in VB6
item.dc:creator: @Bebemycat2 Bebe
item.description:
@Bebemycat2 wrote:

I searched the registry for "ieframe.dll\1" an removed the "\1" from the found key now working
or
Here are the step I make to solve the problem: 1) Reference the "Microsoft Internet Controls" from "C:\Windows\System32\ieframe.dll\1" to "C:\Windows\System32\shdocvw.dll". Save your VB6 project. 2) Run your VB6 project. Re-install your IE7 if got any "runtime error" occurred. (Most possible it will trigger an error while you try to "navigate" using the Webbrowser for the second time.) 3) After you re-installed the IE7, the VB6 project will properly refering back to the "C:\Windows\System32\ieframe.dll" again. Don't worry about it and you should run the project perfectly without any error. 4) Try to compile your VB6 project then Save it. 5) Re-open your VB6 project again, if it run well, then the problem solved. If it is not, try to do the step one again and then save your VB6 project.

Those should work.
